	<region id="editorData">
		<node id="editorData">
			<attribute id="HowToTrigger" type="LSString" value="1. Venture forth as a Druid Human Male&#xD;&#xA;2. In recon &quot;loadlevel WDL_Main_A&quot;&#xD;&#xA;3. In recon &quot;goto -437.00, 1.46, -6.00&quot;&#xD;&#xA;4. CTRL +SHIFT+ L on Avatar to level up&#xD;&#xA;5. In recon &quot;roll 20&quot;&#xD;&#xA;6. Pickpocket the &quot;Elixir of Silvanus&quot; from Nettie to be used to cure the poison later&#xD;&#xA;7. Speak with Nettie and explain the Tadpole.&#xD;&#xA;8. Follow Nettie in other room, dialog starts&#xD;&#xA;(If Nettie triggers crime dialog, persuade her otherwise and full rest camp inside to restart Nettie's pathing)&#xD;&#xA;9. Select dialog #4 “Is everyone being captured…”&#xD;&#xA;10. Select dialog #3 “Just hurry up and cure me…”&#xD;&#xA;11. Select dialog #3 “No, nothing strange…”&#xD;&#xA;12. Select dialog &quot;Nothing, I'm sure.&quot;&#xD;&#xA;13. Select dialog #1 “Hold out your arm”&#xD;&#xA;14. Select dialog #3 “Grab the branch from her…”&#xD;&#xA;15. Select dialog #4 &quot;Turn and leave&quot;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;16. Wildshape into a Wolf or any form&#xD;&#xA;17. Drink the  Elixir of Silvanus&#xD;&#xA;18. Observe dialog will be triggered with an in-game view" />
			<attribute id="needLayout" type="bool" value="False" />
			<attribute id="nextNodeId" type="uint32" value="29" />
			<attribute id="synopsis" type="LSString" value="The player is locked in Nettie's lab and has cured themselves before persuading her. Normally, script starts the dialog 'DEN_Apprentice_LockedUp' to react to this, but it can fail if the player is wild shaped for example. This node taken from the dialog 'DEN_CGB_Apprentice' gives the feedback thatNettie is going hostile." />
			<children>
				<node id="defaultAttitudes">
					<children>
						<node id="data">
							<attribute id="key" type="FixedString" value="0" />
							<attribute id="val" type="LSString" value="Neutral" />
